 
<!-- PJG STAG 4700 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=52 g=1 f=1 -->
Subpart B_Application Requirements and Procedures
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;22.101 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Station files.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Applications, notifications, correspondence and other material, and copies of authorizations, comprising technical,
legal, and administrative data relating to each station in the Public Mobile Services are maintained by the FCC in
individual station files. These files constitute the official records for these stations and supersede any other
records, data bases or lists from the FCC or other sources.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;22.103 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Representations.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Applicants must make full and continuing disclosure as required by &sect;1.65 of this chapter. Applicants must not
make misrepresentations. The signing of an application or notification for new or additional facilities in the Public
Mobile Services constitutes a representation that the applicant intends to use such facilities to provide service
to subscribers in accordance with the rules in this part.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;22.105 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Written applications, standard forms, microfiche, magnetic disks.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Except for authorizations granted under the emergency conditions set forth in section 308 of the Communications
Act of 1934, as amended (47 U.S.C. 308), the FCC may grant authorizations only upon written application (FCC Form 401)
received by it. A separate written application is required for each authorization. Applicants shall submit any documents,
exhibits, or other written statements of fact that the FCC may require in determining whether to grant, deny or dismiss
an application.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

